'''Digital Homicide Studios L.L.C.'''，是一家总部位于美国[[亚利桑那州|亚利桑那州]][[尤馬縣_(亞利桑那州)|尤马]]的[[游戏开发商|游戏开发商]]，由Robert Romine和James Oliver Romine Jr成立于2014年5月29日。该公司曾使用多个假名，包括'''Imminent Uprising'''和'''ECC Games'''（后更名为'''Every Click Counts Games'''）。该公司的第一款游戏《Forsaken Uprising》于2014年8月14日在[[Steam|Steam]] Early Access发布，并在2014年12月3日完全发布。

2016年3月4日，该公司的James Romine起诉[[YouTube|YouTube]]频道、游戏评论家Jim Sterling“攻击、诽谤和中伤”，要求赔偿1000万[[美元|美元]]，<ref name="Kotaku">{{cite web | url = http://kotaku.com/angered-game-developer-sues-game-critic-jim-sterling-fo-1765484317 | title = Angered Game Developer Sues Critic Jim Sterling For $10 Million | last = Klepek | first = Patrick | date = March 17, 2016 | website = [[Kotaku|Kotaku]] | publisher = [[Gawker_Media|Gawker Media]] | accessdate = May 1, 2016 | archive-date = 2016-03-19 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160319060759/http://kotaku.com/angered-game-developer-sues-game-critic-jim-sterling-fo-1765484317 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Destructoid">{{cite web | url = http://www.destructoid.com/indie-developer-digital-homicide-sues-jim-sterling-349283.phtml | title = Indie developer Digital Homicide sues Jim Sterling | last = Cosimano | first = Mike | date = March 17, 2016 | website = [[Destructoid|Destructoid]] | publisher = [[ModernMethod|ModernMethod]] | accessdate = May 1, 2016 | archive-date = 2016-03-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160318170837/http://www.destructoid.com/indie-developer-digital-homicide-sues-jim-sterling-349283.phtml | dead-url = no }}</ref>后来又升至1500万美元。<ref name="TechRaptor 1">{{cite web | url = http://techraptor.net/content/digital-homicides-games-removed-steam | title = [Updated] Digital Homicide's Games Removed From Steam | last = Parsons | first = Don | date = September 16, 2016 | website = [[TechRaptor|TechRaptor]] | accessdate = September 17, 2016 | archive-date = 2016-09-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160917081357/http://techraptor.net/content/digital-homicides-games-removed-steam | dead-url = no }}</ref>2016年9月12日，Romine以“人身伤害”额外起诉100名[[Steam|Steam]]用户，要求总和1800万美元。<ref name="TechRaptor 2">{{cite web | url = https://techraptor.net/content/digital-homicide-suing-100-steam-users-18-million | title = Digital Homicide Suing 100 Steam Users for 18 Million | last = Grosso | first = Robert | date = September 16, 2016 | website = [[TechRaptor|TechRaptor]] | accessdate = September 17, 2016 | archive-date = 2016-09-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160917023332/http://techraptor.net/content/digital-homicide-suing-100-steam-users-18-million | dead-url = no }}</ref>[[Valve|Valve]]拒绝提供100个用户的身份。<ref name="TechRaptor 2" /><ref name="Polygon">{{cite web | url = http://www.polygon.com/2016/9/17/12951756/digital-homicide-lawsuit-jim-sterling-steam-users-valve | title = Steam removes games of developer seeking subpoena for users' information (Correction) | last = Good | first = Owen S. | date = September 17, 2016 | website = [[Polygon_(website)|Polygon]] | publisher = [[Vox_Media|Vox Media]] | accessdate = September 23, 2016 | archive-date = 2016-09-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160923181330/http://www.polygon.com/2016/9/17/12951756/digital-homicide-lawsuit-jim-sterling-steam-users-valve | dead-url = no }}</ref>当天晚些时候，Valve将该工作室所有游戏从Steam商店下架，並對此回應“由於该公司敌视Steam用户，因此終止與該公司合作的業務”。<ref name="TechRaptor 1" />10月2日，Digital Homicide Studios放弃起诉Steam用户，Romine称该公司已“毁”于诉讼。<ref name="Polygon2">{{cite web | url = http://www.polygon.com/2016/10/3/13153766/digital-homicide-lawsuit-sue-threats-subpoena-steam-users-jim-sterling | title = Developer seeking Steam users' identities for lawsuit withdraws case, saying his studio 'is destroyed' | last = Good | first = Owen S. | date = October 3, 2016 | website = [[Polygon_(website)|Polygon]] | publisher = [[Vox_Media|Vox Media]] | accessdate = October 3, 2016 | archive-date = 2016-10-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161005094253/http://www.polygon.com/2016/10/3/13153766/digital-homicide-lawsuit-sue-threats-subpoena-steam-users-jim-sterling | dead-url = no }}</ref>

== 诉讼 ==
该工作室的第一个正式发布的游戏《The Slaughtering Grounds》于2014年10月31日面世。<ref name="steamstore">{{cite web|title=The Slaughtering Grounds on Steam|url=http://store.steampowered.com/app/329950|website=Steam Store|accessdate=2014-11-01|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141101152244/http://store.steampowered.com/app/329950|language=en|date=2014-11-01|archivedate=2014-11-01|deadurl=yes}}</ref>游戏发布后评论家Jim Sterling（原为The Escapist撰稿人）援引了游戏低劣的画质、程序的错误、糟糕的操控、简短循环的音乐以及大量使用他人制作的模型及材质的情况，<ref name="The Escapist">{{cite web | url = http://www.escapistmagazine.com/videos/view/jimquisition/9884-The-Slaughtering-Grounds-Developer-Meltdown | title = ''The Slaughtering Grounds'': A Steam Meltdown Story | last = Sterling | first = Jim | date = November 10, 2014 | website = [[The_Escapist_(magazine)|The Escapist]] | publisher = [[Defy_Media|Defy Media]] | accessdate = May 1, 2016 | archive-date = 2016-06-30 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160630150954/http://www.escapistmagazine.com/videos/view/jimquisition/9884-The-Slaughtering-Grounds-Developer-Meltdown | dead-url = no }}</ref>将该游戏列为“新的‘2014年最烂游戏’竞逐者”。<ref name="Kotaku" />Sterling同时指责开发者删除对游戏的负面评价并封禁批评该游戏的用户。<ref name="The Escapist" />作为回应，游戏的开发者对Sterling在YouTube的视频发起了侵权删除通知。<ref name="Kotaku" />

2016年3月4日，James Romine以“攻击、诽谤和中伤”为由起诉Jim Sterling，起初索赔1000万美元，<ref name="Kotaku" /><ref name="Destructoid" />而后增加到1500万美元。<ref name="TechRaptor 1" />2016年9月12日，Romine又对100位Steam用户以“人身伤害”为理由提出控告并索赔1800万美元，<ref name="TechRaptor 2" />并以此传唤Valve要求其提供这100名用户的身份信息。<ref name="TechRaptor 2" /><ref name="Polygon" />当天晚些时候，Valve将该工作室的21个游戏和15个[[可下载内容|DLC]]移出Steam商店，并解释称Valve“由于Digital Homicide敌视Steam用户而终止与其的商业关系”。<ref name="TechRaptor 1" />2016年10月2日，Digital Homicide放弃起诉Steam用户，Romine称其工作室已“毁”于诉讼。<ref name="Polygon2" />

2017年2月21日，由于数月的技术挫折导致的法律拖延，James Romine与Sterling的辩护律师达成协议，以“有损害模式”终止诉讼——Romine同意不会再对Sterling提出任何诉讼和指控，且不会在未考虑Sterling是否符合[[合理使用|合理使用]]的情况下对其作品发起[[数字千年版权法|DMCA]]侵权通知。<ref name="Eurogamer">{{cite web | url = http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-02-22-long-running-lawsuit-between-jim-sterling-and-digital-homicide-finally-comes-to-an-end | title = Jim Sterling comes out on top as lawsuit with Digital Homicide dismissed | last = Yin-Poole | first = Wesley | date = February 22, 2017 | website = [[Eurogamer|Eurogamer]] | publisher = [[Gamer_Network|Gamer Network]] | accessdate = February 22, 2017 | archive-date = 2017-02-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170223212419/http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2017-02-22-long-running-lawsuit-between-jim-sterling-and-digital-homicide-finally-comes-to-an-end | dead-url = no }}</ref>

